<L>__{interior the tepee med. close shot the group as before}
<A>__{scar is watching the white men like a hawk. martin's eyes are wide and his breathing seems suspended. but ethan is playing it like a poker player.}
<C>__{ethan}
<P>__{(his voice controlled)}
<D>__{i've seen scalps before...}
<A>__{scar's eyes are mocking. he lets his robe slip back from his shoulders, revealing a bare bronzed chest on which glinting in the reflected firelight is the medallion that ethan had given debbie. it is suspended by a chain or rawhide string. scar touches it.}
<C>__{scar}
<D>__{this before?}
<A>__{ethan smiles and he's still playing poker. he stands... and the others follow. scar is puzzled.}
<C>__{ethan}
<P>__{(to emilio)}
<D>__{i came to trade, not to admire his collection... tell him we're going to pitch camp across the crick... maybe we can talk trade tomorrow.}
<A>__{scar hasn't understood all of it. he scowls and looks at emilio.}
<C>__{scar}
<P>__{(in comanche)}
<D>__{ee sap! pabbo tie bo ee sap!}
<P>__{(he lies! the gringo lies!)}
<C>__{emilio}
<P>__{(placatingly)}
<D>__{tomorrow manana 'puetze.'}
<A>__{scar looks at ethan and at martin. he smiles slightly, and he nods his agreement.}
<C>__{scar}
<D>__{puetze!}
<A>__{martin and ethan turn to go. only then does debbie look swiftly at them and as swiftly away. martin can't help but pause, but ethan prods him toward the tepee flap.}
